message.content: cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SD. The paper focuses on developing a conversational AI system that can answer questions rationally by incorporating common sense reasoning. This involves using automated reasoning to understand dialogues and infer facts not explicitly stated. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves machine learning techniques to improve the system's performance, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The system also involves information retrieval (IR) to find relevant information to answer questions, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper involves developing a robust system, which could fall under cs.SD (Software Engineering).
